WEBVTT

00:00.265 --> 00:02.265
_

00:02.394 --> 00:05.554
- You're sure it was Frances?
- Annie, she told me she did it.

00:06.093 --> 00:08.788
She's killing people
who aren't ready to die.

00:08.813 --> 00:11.435
She thinks she's some
kind of angel of mercy.

00:11.470 --> 00:14.234
I struggle with my
obligation to report to.

00:14.259 --> 00:18.309
Like if I suspect a nurse is feeding
terminal patients to a killer.

00:18.946 --> 00:20.211
Should I say something?

00:21.547 --> 00:24.197
Oh, my God. What happened?

00:24.222 --> 00:25.390
You want to be a doctor, right?

00:25.414 --> 00:26.816
You want to be a doctor?
Stitch up my arm.

00:26.840 --> 00:27.999
This will be good practice.

00:29.488 --> 00:32.144
- What are you doing here, Mary?
- I didn't tell you

00:32.168 --> 00:35.761
about the pregnancy because
I was protecting myself.

00:35.786 --> 00:38.905
If you want to be a part of
this baby's life, you can.

00:38.930 --> 00:40.996
It's entirely your decision.

00:41.031 --> 00:42.798
This was my dream.

00:43.466 --> 00:46.245
A safe place where we can do what we do.

00:46.388 --> 00:49.004
What I didn't anticipate
were the people.

00:49.749 --> 00:52.675
The messy, lovely people

00:52.710 --> 00:54.577
that I'd be forced to get to know.

00:54.612 --> 00:56.133
(MACHINE BEEPING RAPIDLY)

00:56.158 --> 00:59.248
A 25 year-old girl is
dead because of us!

00:59.505 --> 01:01.239
You better tell me what's going on.

01:03.855 --> 01:06.389
(SOFT MUSIC)

01:06.424 --> 01:09.024
(BIRD CHIRPING)

01:11.000 --> 01:17.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:29.579 --> 01:32.414
(SOFT MUSIC)

01:42.559 --> 01:45.326
(GROANING) I thought we
agreed on the speed limit.

01:46.102 --> 01:47.321
You could use the thrill.

01:47.346 --> 01:49.932
No, I'm thrilled that we
didn't hit a bloody tree.

01:51.352 --> 01:52.867
- Oh!
- Hey, easy.

01:53.177 --> 01:56.377
No, I'm fine. I'm good. I'm fine.

01:57.239 --> 01:59.173
Just a little stiff from the cold.

01:59.198 --> 02:01.767
- Maybe this wasn't the best idea.
- (SCOFFS)

02:01.792 --> 02:04.701
Me doing anything has
never been the best idea.

02:05.251 --> 02:08.482
I'm not sure what listening to that
little voice has ever gotten me.

02:08.517 --> 02:10.017
You mean the voice of reason?

02:10.785 --> 02:13.020
Fear, reason. What's the difference?

02:13.399 --> 02:16.866
What is it with North Americans
and extreme sports? It's barbaric.

02:16.891 --> 02:20.393
Would you please just shut
up and appreciate this?

02:20.845 --> 02:22.164
I mean, look!

02:23.999 --> 02:27.367
- (BIRD CHIRPING)
- (SOFT MUSIC)

02:27.402 --> 02:30.370
(HEAVY BREATHING)

02:49.424 --> 02:51.191
(SOFT MUSIC)

03:00.004 --> 03:01.104
What?

03:02.824 --> 03:03.977
You need to kill me.

03:05.316 --> 03:06.383
Today.

03:06.408 --> 03:09.009
(ROCK MUSIC)

03:10.939 --> 03:13.939
♪ Mary Kills People 3x04 ♪
<font color="#a4290b">Switzerland Has Trees</font>

03:13.964 --> 03:18.964
- Synced and corrected by<font color="#00BFFF"> Firefly </font>-
- <font color="#00ffff">www.addic7ed.com</font> -

03:22.876 --> 03:26.192
I don't care who's next on the
schedule. Is Lucy's day today.

03:26.217 --> 03:28.472
No, it's actually Phil's day.
He's already been told.

03:29.012 --> 03:32.410
Lucy's been here longer.
So, that's what's fair.

03:33.231 --> 03:36.101
I'm sorry, but that's
the way it has to be.

03:38.234 --> 03:40.134
Look, I promised, all right?

03:42.927 --> 03:45.062
Fine. We'll push Phil

03:45.087 --> 03:47.874
if Mary signs off on it, but
he is in pretty rough shape.

03:47.899 --> 03:49.454
They're all in rough shape!
They're dying!

03:49.478 --> 03:51.524
Do you want to talk about
what's really going on here?

03:51.548 --> 03:55.087
No. No, I really don't. We
need to have a little chat.

03:58.426 --> 03:59.492
Oh...

04:00.658 --> 04:02.225
Yeah, maybe you should talk first.

04:02.869 --> 04:05.129
Desmond. Nicole.

04:05.252 --> 04:08.099
Ben. You look shaggier.

04:08.347 --> 04:10.780
- What, are you two back together?
- This isn't about that.

04:10.804 --> 04:14.573
Oh, dear God! This is
about the nurse, isn't it?

04:14.598 --> 04:15.765
What nurse?

04:17.310 --> 04:19.510
- (TENSE MUSIC)
- Mary, what the hell is going on?

04:23.701 --> 04:25.029
Did you put one in for me?

04:25.937 --> 04:27.852
Are we seriously not
gonna talk about this?

04:27.877 --> 04:29.944
- Is that a no on the bagel?
- Read this.

04:29.969 --> 04:31.602
Cambie, we're going to be late. Come on.

04:35.099 --> 04:38.362
Okay. "Had to work early.
Lunch is in the fridge.

04:38.398 --> 04:41.633
Have good days, girls.
Love you, Mom." What?

04:41.658 --> 04:44.012
Why is everyone acting
like nothing's changed?

04:44.037 --> 04:45.837
We met Mom's baby daddy last night.

04:45.862 --> 04:49.006
- Hello, weirdness?
- Can you just please stop calling him that?

04:49.041 --> 04:51.976
Fine. What do you think about this?

04:52.521 --> 04:55.590
(HEAVY SIGH) I think it's nice.

04:55.615 --> 04:57.715
You know, the stuff that
Mom has to deal with,

04:57.740 --> 04:59.766
it's... it's a lot,

04:59.791 --> 05:03.954
and I think maybe it'd be good
if she had someone to help her.

05:03.990 --> 05:05.608
- I guess so.
- (TOASTER POPPING)

05:06.861 --> 05:08.019
Thank you.

05:08.044 --> 05:09.361
Now, come on. We gotta go.

05:10.482 --> 05:12.817
We'll compare notes
about Ben on the way. Okay?

05:16.136 --> 05:18.069
Does he really live in a trailer?

05:19.165 --> 05:21.244
So, this nurse, Frances,

05:21.269 --> 05:24.509
killed an innocent non-terminal
patient at the hospital.

05:24.534 --> 05:28.102
And framed Annie for it.
Which means if the police

05:28.127 --> 05:30.127
are looking into her, then
they'll come back here,

05:30.319 --> 05:32.587
given she is your main
source of patients.

05:32.612 --> 05:34.124
Does he know everything?

05:34.814 --> 05:36.170
- He does.
- (SIGHS)

05:38.021 --> 05:40.354
So, you've been helping
people on the side?

05:44.853 --> 05:47.072
Well, that explains the missing Pento.

05:47.097 --> 05:49.344
So you've just been lying
to us this whole time?

05:50.820 --> 05:52.355
I mean, did you know?

05:53.839 --> 05:55.240
(SIGHS)

05:56.840 --> 05:59.219
Amazing. You guys are seriously amazing.

05:59.244 --> 06:00.789
Let me just get something straight here.

06:00.813 --> 06:04.578
I am currently the sole
registered owner of a hospice

06:04.603 --> 06:06.735
that may be being targeted by the police

06:06.760 --> 06:08.508
or a psychopath or maybe both,

06:08.533 --> 06:10.642
and what's worse is I can't even trust

06:10.667 --> 06:13.468
the two people that convinced
me to do this in the first place.

06:13.493 --> 06:16.559
Look Nicole, I know this is tough
but we will deal with it, okay?

06:16.782 --> 06:19.139
Right now, and just-just for now,

06:20.250 --> 06:22.965
we need to stop helping your patients.

06:23.501 --> 06:25.168
Okay? Keep the business open,

06:25.610 --> 06:28.605
a completely legitimate
hospice, above board.

06:29.204 --> 06:31.674
But no assisted deaths, none,

06:32.584 --> 06:35.111
until we are sure no one
is looking into the place.

06:35.136 --> 06:36.386
Is this him helping?

06:36.411 --> 06:38.605
Because I preferred when he
just stood there brooding.

06:38.630 --> 06:40.584
Des, can you please listen?

06:41.820 --> 06:44.453
- Nicole!
- (DOOR CREAKING)

06:44.488 --> 06:45.591
(DOOR SLAMMING)

06:47.905 --> 06:52.407
So, we're gonna just sit
and watch our patients die?

06:54.665 --> 06:58.534
(SIGHS) What happened to helping people?

07:01.930 --> 07:04.273
- We'll figure this out.
- We?

07:04.773 --> 07:06.041
You and Ben?

07:08.364 --> 07:10.155
I'm just supposed to trust him now?

07:10.180 --> 07:13.349
Yes. Unless you want to go to prison.

07:14.328 --> 07:15.395
Again.

07:19.790 --> 07:20.891
Hey...

07:23.310 --> 07:24.732
It is going to be okay.

07:26.615 --> 07:29.165
I'm not sure about anything
anymore. I feel like I've...

07:29.714 --> 07:32.180
done everything wrong, and
I don't know how to fix it.

07:32.205 --> 07:33.507
We will fix it.

07:34.195 --> 07:35.508
Okay? We'll figure it out.

07:38.878 --> 07:40.853
Des and Nicole must think I'm crazy

07:40.878 --> 07:43.711
for putting my faith
in you after everything.

07:45.010 --> 07:46.514
Well, things are...

07:46.846 --> 07:47.947
different now.

07:50.552 --> 07:54.576
- I guess they are.
- I'm gonna put Hull onto Frances, okay?

07:55.139 --> 07:57.907
- And I will see you later.
- (SOFT MUSIC)

08:04.033 --> 08:06.433
(BIRD CHIRPING)

08:16.378 --> 08:18.145
(LABOURED BREATHING)

08:19.650 --> 08:21.448
Is it okay if I come in?

08:28.749 --> 08:30.024
Is it time?

08:34.126 --> 08:36.542
Phil, I'm sorry but we
can't help you today.

08:37.847 --> 08:39.033
We're working on it.

08:40.424 --> 08:42.803
But you're going to have
to wait a little bit longer.

08:43.424 --> 08:44.839
Maybe a couple days.

08:47.141 --> 08:48.420
Do you understand?

08:48.847 --> 08:50.014
Yeah, I get it.

08:51.237 --> 08:53.022
I guess I'm getting what I deserve.

08:53.347 --> 08:54.762
I'm not sure what you mean.

08:57.710 --> 08:59.304
Phil, you know I believe

08:59.329 --> 09:01.238
people should get to
choose their own death.

09:02.303 --> 09:04.057
I believe every person in here

09:04.178 --> 09:06.046
deserves that, including you.

09:08.167 --> 09:09.197
Forget it.

09:12.934 --> 09:14.301
Is there anything I can...

09:15.579 --> 09:17.806
do in the meantime to...

09:19.384 --> 09:21.040
make you more comfortable?

09:23.473 --> 09:26.009
No. I'm good.

09:34.158 --> 09:35.421
- What are you doing?
- Well,

09:35.446 --> 09:37.013
William here is a lawyer.

09:37.558 --> 09:39.575
It's very convenient. You
should have one on staff.

09:39.600 --> 09:43.002
- I'd stay on if I could.
- Thank you, William.

09:43.580 --> 09:44.614
My pleasure.

09:45.878 --> 09:47.878
(GRUNTING)

09:51.760 --> 09:55.661
Well, I have been thinking
about my last meal.

09:56.010 --> 09:58.076
I did some light death row research.

09:58.101 --> 10:01.068
Did you know John Wayne Gacy
had a dozen fried shrimp,

10:01.385 --> 10:04.283
a bucket of fried chicken
and a pound of strawberries?

10:04.318 --> 10:07.052
- No, I did not know that.
- Well, anyway,

10:07.591 --> 10:09.722
I want a TV dinner.

10:09.757 --> 10:12.186
A Salisbury steak one, you
know, with the puffy potatoes

10:12.211 --> 10:15.561
and that cranberry thing that
gets way too hot in the microwave.

10:16.241 --> 10:17.690
- Ever had one?
- No.

10:17.715 --> 10:21.388
- My parents loved me.
- And I want it on a TV tray

10:21.854 --> 10:23.474
and I want to be watching <i>
The Price is Right.</i>

10:23.498 --> 10:24.818
I have to tell you something.

10:31.679 --> 10:33.478
(SIGHS) Okay. I know I said

10:33.503 --> 10:34.738
that we could do this today...

10:36.987 --> 10:38.055
We can't.

10:40.453 --> 10:41.553
And why not?

10:42.070 --> 10:44.589
- It's confidential.
- Try again.

10:45.195 --> 10:47.826
Okay. Because we have
rules and regulations

10:47.851 --> 10:49.684
- to keep us out of jail.
- Des...

10:50.761 --> 10:52.431
- You promised.
- I know.

10:53.090 --> 10:54.157
And I'm so sorry.

10:56.449 --> 10:59.069
And that's... that's
all I can say right now.

11:00.288 --> 11:02.340
Except it wasn't my
decision, believe me.

11:02.375 --> 11:04.544
Let me tell you what
this actually feels like.

11:06.304 --> 11:08.812
One second, I'm all Zen.

11:09.030 --> 11:12.884
The next, I am terrified.

11:14.370 --> 11:15.427
It's like a...

11:16.175 --> 11:19.000
"You're about to die" style
teeter-totter and I just want

11:19.025 --> 11:21.494
to get the hell off.

11:30.268 --> 11:33.004
I... need it

11:33.610 --> 11:35.850
to be today.

11:37.914 --> 11:39.543
Well, I'm sorry. I can't.

11:39.578 --> 11:43.247
(SOFT MUSIC)

11:43.282 --> 11:46.883
(SIGHS)

11:47.176 --> 11:48.451
Then what good are you?

11:58.745 --> 12:01.380
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

12:01.405 --> 12:05.151
(PHONE RINGING)

12:05.176 --> 12:06.765
(SIGHS) I know where I'm going.

12:06.790 --> 12:08.290
Sorry. Protocol.

12:11.477 --> 12:12.945
- (KNOCKING)
- Come in.

12:17.181 --> 12:18.316
What are you doing here?

12:18.752 --> 12:19.962
You're not expecting him?

12:20.150 --> 12:23.150
Oh, right. Sorry, I forgot
you were stopping by.

12:23.580 --> 12:25.287
- Thanks.
- Here, have a seat.

12:28.065 --> 12:29.325
So, what's up, man?

12:32.013 --> 12:34.606
Something's been bugging
me about this report.

12:38.458 --> 12:41.136
So, Mary Harris,

12:41.161 --> 12:45.172
the hospice, Joys, it all seems legit.

12:45.197 --> 12:47.515
- So you said, yeah.
- Yeah, thing is,

12:47.540 --> 12:48.877
I keep going back over it,

12:48.902 --> 12:52.012
and Gail Rahimi, the insulin overdose?

12:52.540 --> 12:55.416
Yeah, what do you know about this
nurse that was there, Frances Thorp?

12:56.422 --> 12:59.874
Not much. ICU nurse at Eden

12:59.899 --> 13:01.919
and she was there to give meds to her.

13:01.989 --> 13:05.349
Except ICU nurses do not do house calls.

13:06.403 --> 13:09.429
- What are you saying?
- I'm saying maybe,

13:10.570 --> 13:14.210
maybe she was there to
deliver specific medication,

13:14.593 --> 13:16.906
like a lethal dose of insulin.

13:17.374 --> 13:18.613
That's a bit of a stretch.

13:18.638 --> 13:20.908
But maybe not, and it's worth a look.

13:22.184 --> 13:23.443
Come on, man. It's easy.

13:23.468 --> 13:26.435
Personal history, work
history, see if there's been

13:26.460 --> 13:29.261
any suspicious activity since
she started at the hospital.

13:30.136 --> 13:32.058
Then, then it's up to you.

13:32.083 --> 13:36.089
It's your call if there is
anything to be concerned about.

13:36.608 --> 13:38.692
- Okay, I'll look into it.
- Good.

13:40.201 --> 13:41.295
You ever miss it?

13:42.873 --> 13:44.263
Because we make a good team.

13:44.703 --> 13:47.970
Like if this case works out,
maybe you could come back.

13:48.872 --> 13:49.905
Maybe.

14:03.833 --> 14:05.933
- Naomi? Hey, wake up.
- Mm?

14:06.234 --> 14:09.075
- I don't want to.
- Too bad. Come on, get up.

14:09.859 --> 14:11.524
What are you doing here, Jess?

14:11.549 --> 14:13.600
Well, you weren't in school
again, so I got worried.

14:13.862 --> 14:15.411
Yeah, my shoulder still hurts.

14:16.325 --> 14:18.837
Okay, let me take a look at
your stitches. Come here.

14:21.467 --> 14:22.567
Okay...

14:26.983 --> 14:30.244
Hm! That actually looks okay.

14:30.954 --> 14:33.515
- Maybe I should be a doctor.
- Ha!

14:33.540 --> 14:36.111
See, without me, you wouldn't
have found your calling.

14:36.136 --> 14:38.337
And more importantly,
you can go to school tomorrow.

14:38.362 --> 14:39.412
Pass.

14:40.699 --> 14:42.496
Okay, fine. Um...

14:43.816 --> 14:45.369
Okay, how about I make you a deal?

14:45.394 --> 14:48.247
And you can either go to school tomorrow

14:48.419 --> 14:51.395
- or you can call your mom.
- Hard pass.

14:53.593 --> 14:54.760
Hey, look...

14:55.997 --> 14:57.822
I don't know what's
going on with you here,

14:57.847 --> 15:01.238
but you can't stay at
home by yourself anymore.

15:08.282 --> 15:11.555
Okay. Um... I'm gonna, I'm
gonna clean this place up,

15:11.758 --> 15:15.636
make us some food
that isn't pizza and...

15:15.661 --> 15:17.828
And then you can call your mom. Okay?

15:19.851 --> 15:20.985
(WHISPERING): Whatever.

15:21.927 --> 15:24.861
- (GUSTING WIND)
- (CROW CAWING)

15:28.132 --> 15:30.132
(DOOR CLOSES)

15:30.777 --> 15:31.868
Here we go.

15:33.105 --> 15:35.106
Oh, no. I'm not gonna lecture you.

15:35.992 --> 15:38.893
I miss it. I had to quit.

15:41.885 --> 15:43.400
It'll wait for you to come back.

15:48.482 --> 15:51.120
Phil, I really am sorry about all this.

15:52.802 --> 15:55.725
I know you were expecting
today to be the day.

15:56.573 --> 15:58.409
That can't be easy to turn off.

15:59.775 --> 16:01.776
Things don't always go the way you want.

16:04.434 --> 16:08.304
Only thing you can control
is... your reaction.

16:09.215 --> 16:10.955
Is that the military mindset?

16:10.980 --> 16:13.890
It prepares you for anything
that may be thrown your way.

16:16.543 --> 16:17.710
Where did you serve?

16:21.190 --> 16:22.723
We don't have to talk about it.

16:24.096 --> 16:25.187
Oh, Phil!

16:26.588 --> 16:28.758
Come on, Phil. It's okay. I need help!

16:28.783 --> 16:30.592
(TENSE MUSIC)

16:30.627 --> 16:33.929
(LABOURED BREATHING)

16:39.306 --> 16:42.040
- What's that?
- It's called modeling.

16:42.931 --> 16:44.267
It occurs when the body

16:44.292 --> 16:46.509
starts to conserve
blood around the heart.

16:48.217 --> 16:50.083
It's a strong indication that the body

16:50.108 --> 16:51.944
has started the dying process.

16:53.116 --> 16:54.949
It's just a matter of time now.

16:56.014 --> 16:57.019
Well...

16:58.542 --> 16:59.821
That's that, then.

17:09.188 --> 17:10.663
Is there someone I can call?

17:12.077 --> 17:13.497
We're not doing an assisted death,

17:13.521 --> 17:15.969
so there's no reason why you
can't have someone here with you.

17:17.450 --> 17:20.185
(SIGHS) There's no one.

17:27.259 --> 17:30.995
(CRYING)

17:32.598 --> 17:34.221
(SIGHS)

17:35.739 --> 17:37.864
If this is the way it has to be for me,

17:39.100 --> 17:40.246
then so be it.

17:43.645 --> 17:44.832
I've seen worse.

17:46.081 --> 17:47.701
I've done worse. (LABOURED BREATHING)

17:51.878 --> 17:53.106
The first Gulf War.

17:54.935 --> 17:57.677
A lot of people died over
there, too many people.

17:58.536 --> 18:00.519
You serve for the good of your country.

18:00.544 --> 18:03.750
Justified murder, that's
what they called it.

18:04.667 --> 18:06.704
Maybe it was, maybe it wasn't.

18:09.266 --> 18:11.091
I guess I feel like...

18:13.312 --> 18:15.904
the doubt, the questioning, it's...

18:17.515 --> 18:18.880
It's what makes us human,

18:18.905 --> 18:20.900
what makes us worthy of mercy.

18:25.471 --> 18:26.806
Will you stay?

18:27.494 --> 18:30.309
Of course. Of course.

18:35.483 --> 18:36.517
Can I come in?

18:40.586 --> 18:42.163
Can you believe that some people

18:42.188 --> 18:45.588
put solving a 2,000 piece
puzzle on their bucket list?

18:46.455 --> 18:48.327
Maybe not the most interesting people.

18:48.363 --> 18:50.727
But who am I to judge?

18:52.719 --> 18:54.448
Oh, come on, Lucy. Please.

18:54.970 --> 18:58.437
(ENIGMATIC MUSIC)

19:05.046 --> 19:08.481
(ENIGMATIC MUSIC)

19:30.571 --> 19:34.573
(MECHANICAL WHIRRING)

19:35.077 --> 19:36.710
You're joking. Really?

19:37.149 --> 19:40.211
- I canceled my credit cards.
- Just get in.

19:40.236 --> 19:42.261
No, thanks. I'll wait for the next one.

19:48.722 --> 19:51.990
It doesn't seem like you
have much of a plan here.

19:52.514 --> 19:53.721
What are you doing, exactly?

19:53.946 --> 19:56.762
Well, I've been thinking
of hanging myself from a tree.

19:59.267 --> 20:01.009
I promise I will not take you back.

20:04.559 --> 20:06.504
Well, promises aren't your strong suit.

20:07.793 --> 20:08.907
Lucy, please.

20:21.698 --> 20:24.398
- Now, where to?
- I'll direct you.

20:32.709 --> 20:37.611
♪♪

20:37.636 --> 20:42.539
♪♪

20:42.564 --> 20:45.748
(SOFT PIANO MUSIC)

20:45.819 --> 20:48.820
(FAST-PACED PIANO MUSIC)

21:20.414 --> 21:24.327
- ♪ Misty moon ♪
- (LABOURED BREATHING)

21:24.352 --> 21:25.419
I'm right here.

21:25.819 --> 21:27.153
I'm not going anywhere.

21:28.123 --> 21:32.225
♪ Spills through old windows ♪

21:32.604 --> 21:33.771
Is it happening?

21:34.387 --> 21:36.623
The truth is you'll know better than me.

21:38.383 --> 21:41.550
♪ Of our earthly room ♪

21:41.735 --> 21:42.801
It's okay.

21:43.737 --> 21:45.003
Do you feel any pain?

21:45.492 --> 21:46.558
Yes.

21:47.928 --> 21:52.764
(LABOURED BREATHING)

21:52.789 --> 21:56.724
♪ Spill to you on the right side ♪

22:01.400 --> 22:02.601
I'm afraid.

22:03.438 --> 22:05.505
Most people will feel fear...

22:06.829 --> 22:07.829
and then calm.

22:10.508 --> 22:13.564
♪ Of our bed ♪

22:15.129 --> 22:17.696
This will end soon, I promise.

22:41.718 --> 22:43.219
What, are you gonna rob this place?

22:43.914 --> 22:45.421
I didn't see it on the bucket list.

22:45.446 --> 22:47.168
I left my balaclava at the retreat.

22:47.585 --> 22:48.832
This is my house.

22:49.967 --> 22:53.769
(ENIGMATIC MUSIC)

23:04.749 --> 23:06.716
(DOOR CLOSES)

23:09.664 --> 23:12.998
- This is your house?
- It was my grandparents' house,

23:13.267 --> 23:15.402
then my parents', and now mine.

23:15.864 --> 23:18.248
Well, I for one love what
you've done with the place.

23:18.273 --> 23:20.774
It's... very minimalist.

23:21.249 --> 23:24.317
I let the staff have whatever
they wanted after I left.

23:24.829 --> 23:26.234
How rich are you, exactly?

23:26.743 --> 23:30.478
I am the secret heiress to the
Swanson's TV dinner fortune.

23:30.574 --> 23:32.693
- Seriously?
- (SNORTS)

23:32.718 --> 23:35.520
No! I wish. It's much
more boring than that.

23:42.250 --> 23:45.617
So, why did you come to
Joys if you have all of this?

23:45.739 --> 23:47.705
(CHUCKLING) Please.

23:47.860 --> 23:50.275
The heiress who pops pills
and dies alone in her mansion?

23:50.300 --> 23:52.451
That is such a cliché.

23:54.860 --> 23:56.160
And yet, here we are.

24:00.445 --> 24:02.299
Okay. Honestly?

24:03.874 --> 24:05.268
I was scared to do it alone.

24:06.146 --> 24:07.472
Afraid I was gonna screw it up.

24:08.607 --> 24:12.207
And what Annie described with
the doctors and the retreat

24:12.232 --> 24:15.879
and a definitive end date, it
just sounded pretty damn good.

24:16.104 --> 24:19.516
But you clearly could have flown
first class to Switzerland.

24:20.705 --> 24:23.554
There's no messy human
connections there.

24:31.940 --> 24:33.698
I didn't come to you to make friends.

24:35.269 --> 24:37.803
I came so I could have
a safe, peaceful end.

24:41.688 --> 24:43.235
And I like trees.

24:44.532 --> 24:46.009
Can we just leave it at that?

24:46.035 --> 24:47.320
Sure.

24:48.441 --> 24:50.160
Switzerland has trees.

24:51.137 --> 24:53.350
- Just saying.
- (LUCY CHUCKLES)

24:53.532 --> 24:56.770
This is the only room
in the house that I like.

24:57.279 --> 24:59.454
- You coming in?
- Uh, no,

24:59.774 --> 25:01.090
I am not much of a soaker.

25:01.257 --> 25:03.857
Oh, you should try it. It's saltwater.

25:05.851 --> 25:08.197
It's like a pool full of my tears.

25:08.232 --> 25:11.600
(SOFT MUSIC)

25:17.210 --> 25:20.045
(COUGHING AND GASPING)

25:40.196 --> 25:43.331
(GASPING)

25:56.575 --> 25:58.742
(HEAVY EXHALE)

26:13.587 --> 26:14.729
Phil died.

26:17.164 --> 26:18.211
Did you hear me?

26:21.563 --> 26:22.649
What are you doing?

26:22.774 --> 26:24.672
I can't believe you took the Pento.

26:25.652 --> 26:28.776
Everything is on the line right now
and you couldn't even last one day.

26:29.050 --> 26:31.744
- I didn't do anything.
- Stop lying to me.

26:31.769 --> 26:32.914
I'm not lying.

26:34.078 --> 26:35.961
I wish I was, but I'm not.

26:36.938 --> 26:38.789
I swear, Nicole, I didn't do anything

26:38.814 --> 26:41.655
but hold that man's hand
and watch him struggle

26:41.691 --> 26:45.173
as he died naturally... and in pain.

26:54.434 --> 26:57.647
We're supposed to help them.
That's why they came here.

26:57.672 --> 27:00.371
Yeah, well, you took that away
from them one lie at a time.

27:00.396 --> 27:01.578
Although, you have managed

27:01.603 --> 27:03.787
to tell your ex-cop
boyfriend the whole truth.

27:03.812 --> 27:05.589
I told Ben because I
need someone in my life

27:05.614 --> 27:07.492
who can actually do something
to help for a change,

27:07.516 --> 27:09.717
not just someone who
makes me feel like shit.

27:10.584 --> 27:12.255
You know what? Maybe
you need to grow up.

27:12.987 --> 27:14.532
Take some agency in your life

27:14.752 --> 27:16.503
- and stop blaming me.
- Then let me.

27:18.455 --> 27:21.060
Stop hiding things from me.

27:21.599 --> 27:24.340
Stop treating me like
I'm some little kid

27:24.372 --> 27:26.339
that you have to protect,
and stop making me feel

27:26.367 --> 27:28.468
like I don't have a say
in what happens here.

27:29.962 --> 27:31.571
That may have worked for
us before, it's just...

27:31.595 --> 27:33.043
it's not working for me right now.

27:42.907 --> 27:43.983
Okay.

27:45.236 --> 27:46.653
You're right.

27:50.948 --> 27:52.091
I'm sorry.

27:54.038 --> 27:57.211
We've gone through way
harder stuff than this.

27:58.461 --> 27:59.699
And we did it together.

28:01.078 --> 28:02.634
So don't go, all right?

28:04.612 --> 28:06.129
The patients need you.

28:08.512 --> 28:09.608
I need you.

28:10.949 --> 28:12.044
So...

28:12.285 --> 28:13.380
please stay.

28:15.958 --> 28:17.262
No more secrets.

28:19.442 --> 28:20.752
No more secrets.

28:22.397 --> 28:23.470
Wait.

28:25.791 --> 28:28.694
If you didn't take the
Pento, then who did?

28:31.464 --> 28:34.031
(SOFT MUSIC)

28:36.937 --> 28:40.180
- Why the saltwater?
- My dad had it installed

28:40.205 --> 28:41.839
for my mom's lupus.

28:42.385 --> 28:44.448
Two-for-one investment, as it turns out.

28:44.979 --> 28:47.512
- She has lupus as well, then?
- Had.

28:48.979 --> 28:50.179
She's dead.

28:51.477 --> 28:53.184
Got it from my mom, as they say.

28:53.982 --> 28:55.484
Hers attacked her brain,
though, in the end,

28:55.508 --> 28:57.222
whereas mine went for the kidneys.

28:58.787 --> 29:00.958
Disease of a thousand faces, right?

29:01.820 --> 29:02.820
Right.

29:08.243 --> 29:09.734
I kind of hate my mother.

29:12.331 --> 29:14.328
I mean, she knew it could be
inherited, but she...

29:14.614 --> 29:16.580
went ahead and had a kid anyway.

29:17.726 --> 29:19.177
I guess she wanted a family.

29:20.538 --> 29:23.981
- What about your dad?
- Oh, he was gone a year later.

29:24.413 --> 29:26.683
Died of a broken heart, they said.

29:26.719 --> 29:29.853
(CHUCKLE) Can you believe that shit?

29:30.421 --> 29:33.233
Yeah. I think I can.

29:35.947 --> 29:38.327
No. Don't do that.

29:38.549 --> 29:42.331
- I know what pity looks like.
- It's not pity.

29:45.624 --> 29:46.802
Look...

29:46.827 --> 29:49.072
I know I'm terrible at promises.

29:50.132 --> 29:51.741
You still want to do this today...

29:53.796 --> 29:54.862
We can.

29:57.297 --> 30:00.582
Safe, peaceful.

30:00.617 --> 30:03.051
(ROCK MUSIC)

30:21.475 --> 30:23.975
(ELECTRO-POP MUSIC PLAYING)

30:24.010 --> 30:26.278
- ♪ To our home ♪
- You hate it.

30:27.972 --> 30:30.681
No, it's good. I just...
I'm just not very hungry.

30:30.706 --> 30:32.613
It's disgusting, I get it.

30:32.849 --> 30:36.186
♪ I came here all alone ♪

30:37.220 --> 30:39.588
Okay... It's time to call your mom.

30:39.613 --> 30:42.180
- Jesus, Jess, can you get off my back?
- Naomi, just...

30:43.871 --> 30:47.434
- ♪ Who I'm with ♪
- Fine.

30:48.934 --> 30:52.104
♪ Will I remember it ♪

30:52.129 --> 30:54.539
♪ Trying to get you in ♪

30:54.574 --> 30:56.708
(PHONE LINE TRILLING)

30:58.162 --> 30:59.637
Savard, Johnson and Pelletier.

30:59.662 --> 31:01.738
Hi, may I please speak to Louise Malik?

31:01.763 --> 31:03.803
I believe she's with a client.
Can I take a message?

31:04.175 --> 31:05.216
Okay.

31:06.777 --> 31:10.403
Okay, could you just ask her if
she could talk for a second?

31:10.428 --> 31:12.729
- It's her daughter.
- Oh, sure. One moment.

31:15.461 --> 31:18.929
♪ I don't know ♪

31:24.513 --> 31:26.340
Hi, Naomi? I'm sorry,

31:26.365 --> 31:28.139
Louise says she'll
call you later tonight.

31:29.915 --> 31:31.875
Okay, that's fine. Whatever. (SNIFFLE)

31:37.157 --> 31:38.289
Naomi, you okay?

31:56.256 --> 31:57.290
Naomi!

32:01.606 --> 32:05.175
(CAR DRIVING PAST)

32:11.113 --> 32:14.113
♪ Burn up with the water ♪

32:16.128 --> 32:20.732
♪ The floods are on the plains ♪

32:22.047 --> 32:25.561
♪ The planets in a rose ♪

32:26.250 --> 32:29.831
♪ Who knows what they contain? ♪

32:30.741 --> 32:33.130
♪ And my brain is ♪

32:33.155 --> 32:36.381
♪ Like an orchestra ♪

32:36.983 --> 32:40.473
♪ Playing on insane ♪

32:41.296 --> 32:43.084
♪ Will you love me ♪

32:43.109 --> 32:45.879
- (CARS HONKING)
- ♪ Like you loved me ♪

32:45.915 --> 32:49.946
♪ In the January rain? ♪

32:50.399 --> 32:51.524
Naomi!

32:54.601 --> 32:55.602
Hey!

32:56.250 --> 32:57.858
Hey! Naomi!

32:57.893 --> 33:00.707
- (CARS HONKING)
- (GASP) Naomi!

33:00.732 --> 33:03.931
(CARS HONKING)

33:03.966 --> 33:06.734
(WHIMPER)

33:08.571 --> 33:12.273
♪ The clothespins on the floor ♪

33:12.844 --> 33:14.808
- ♪ In my head ♪
- Naomi!

33:16.488 --> 33:18.946
Stop! Stop!

33:18.981 --> 33:22.750
♪ Wait and count to four ♪

33:22.785 --> 33:25.886
- What the hell are you doing?!
- ♪ Will you love me ♪

33:25.921 --> 33:30.148
- ♪ Like you loved me ♪
- Naomi!

33:32.134 --> 33:33.188
Get...

33:33.213 --> 33:35.195
(HONKING)

33:36.284 --> 33:38.337
♪ Like you loved me ♪

33:38.362 --> 33:41.601
♪ And I'll never ask ♪

33:41.626 --> 33:44.927
♪ For more ♪

34:00.456 --> 34:02.590
You have anything in here
that is an extra small?

34:03.425 --> 34:04.564
Why?

34:04.589 --> 34:07.193
I need something to sleep in.
I'm not leaving you here alone.

34:07.815 --> 34:10.024
- You don't have to do that.
- Yeah, obviously I do.

34:10.049 --> 34:12.002
You were standing out there
in the middle of the road.

34:12.025 --> 34:13.467
It's okay. My mom's coming home.

34:15.190 --> 34:17.367
- You did talk to her then?
- Of course, yeah.

34:17.719 --> 34:19.120
Yeah, she's gonna fly home tonight.

34:21.242 --> 34:22.281
Okay...

34:22.507 --> 34:24.859
That's good. That's... that's great.

34:25.476 --> 34:27.127
No, it'll be good. It'll be really good.

34:27.152 --> 34:31.174
We're going to sit around,
paint our toenails

34:31.199 --> 34:34.878
and we're gonna talk about
how I'm failing school,

34:35.907 --> 34:37.237
I don't have any friends,

34:38.016 --> 34:39.658
I quit dance and...

34:40.742 --> 34:42.952
and I'm an ungrateful bitch.

34:44.234 --> 34:45.663
You have friends.

34:46.906 --> 34:48.274
You have me, right?

34:50.670 --> 34:52.391
Please don't hate me, Jess.

34:54.757 --> 34:56.775
- You really scared me.
- I know.

34:58.797 --> 35:00.437
Yeah, I know. I'm really sorry.

35:01.415 --> 35:04.216
(SOFT MUSIC)

35:10.044 --> 35:13.471
(DES CHUCKLES) Don't you look rich?

35:20.075 --> 35:21.263
I...

35:21.888 --> 35:23.469
don't think I have champagne.

35:25.462 --> 35:27.378
I haven't really been
celebrating lately.

35:27.403 --> 35:29.369
Well, it doesn't matter.
Pick your poison.

35:29.962 --> 35:33.217
- Really?
- No, I, I didn't mean...

35:33.242 --> 35:34.347
I know what you meant.

35:35.924 --> 35:37.764
Don't lose your sense
of humour on me, Bennett.

35:38.711 --> 35:40.285
(SIGHS)

35:47.989 --> 35:49.794
Maybe we should do a shot first.

35:51.694 --> 35:53.973
Yeah, maybe if there
was ever a time for me

35:53.998 --> 35:56.490
to get back in the game,
this would be it.

35:57.412 --> 35:58.503
Nice try.

36:00.542 --> 36:02.742
You're not throwing your life
away on this, you hear me?

36:04.424 --> 36:05.442
Got it.

36:05.477 --> 36:07.778
(SOFT MUSIC)

36:22.147 --> 36:23.227
Des...

36:24.768 --> 36:25.796
Are you okay?

36:26.670 --> 36:27.742
Yeah.

36:29.554 --> 36:32.638
I am so goddamn happy

36:32.663 --> 36:35.504
- I didn't go to Switzerland.
- (BOTH CHUCKLING)

36:38.196 --> 36:39.275
Me too.

36:44.399 --> 36:46.616
(LUCY SNIFFLES) Maybe, uh...

36:47.717 --> 36:49.886
Maybe a quick shot first would be good.

36:56.133 --> 36:57.332
To another day.

37:02.936 --> 37:04.600
- (GLASS SHATTERS)
- (LAUGHING)

37:09.469 --> 37:11.680
God, I've always wanted to do that.

37:12.039 --> 37:14.212
Well, okay, what is happening right now?

37:18.133 --> 37:19.284
I don't know.

37:22.096 --> 37:23.651
I mean, I...

37:25.595 --> 37:26.889
thought I was ready, and then...

37:28.409 --> 37:30.803
I started thinking about
you leaving me here

37:30.828 --> 37:33.663
and that it's gonna be a
week until the maid comes

37:33.688 --> 37:35.157
and I'm going to be covered in flies

37:35.182 --> 37:36.297
and she's gonna have a heart attack

37:36.321 --> 37:37.901
and I would hate that because she's...

37:40.430 --> 37:43.071
she's really nice. (LUCY SNIFFLES)

37:43.107 --> 37:45.640
♪ You've been so sick ♪

37:45.665 --> 37:46.741
Or maybe...

37:49.454 --> 37:51.113
Maybe I just want to
spend another day...

37:52.891 --> 37:53.958
with you.

37:57.187 --> 38:00.088
- ♪ You said to me ♪
- Okay.

38:01.347 --> 38:03.306
♪ Said to me ♪

38:03.331 --> 38:05.560
♪ Let me in for you ♪

38:07.227 --> 38:08.327
Another day, then.

38:10.867 --> 38:13.205
♪ Here I am ♪

38:14.666 --> 38:16.573
♪ Here I am ♪

38:18.941 --> 38:21.476
♪ Waiting for you ♪

38:24.740 --> 38:26.112
Although,

38:26.137 --> 38:27.770
now that I know you're filthy rich,

38:27.795 --> 38:30.485
- I do hope to be written into the will.
- (CHUCKLES)

38:31.707 --> 38:33.182
Should I leave some sticky notes

38:33.207 --> 38:36.558
on a few choice items?
Any taxidermy up for grabs?

38:37.695 --> 38:40.196
(HEAVY SIGH)

38:42.386 --> 38:43.620
So, what we do now?

38:46.078 --> 38:47.311
Anything we want.

38:49.872 --> 38:53.441
♪ Sadness and sorrow ♪

39:12.962 --> 39:17.431
- (MOTOR SHUTS OFF)
- (NEARBY CAR DOOR CLOSES)

39:17.467 --> 39:19.867
(TENSE MUSIC)

39:23.078 --> 39:24.600
Evening, Dr. Harris.

39:25.960 --> 39:29.282
I'm Detective Hull. We
met at Gail Rahimi's house.

39:31.397 --> 39:33.819
That's right. You took my statement.

39:34.132 --> 39:36.872
Yeah. And your friend's, Frances Thorp.

39:36.897 --> 39:39.357
- No, she's not my friend.
- Oh, really?

39:39.882 --> 39:42.383
Well, I mean, I never
met her before that day.

39:42.771 --> 39:45.207
Well, that may actually be true...

39:45.771 --> 39:46.861
I'm, uh...

39:47.930 --> 39:50.439
just a little bit more
concerned with your relationship

39:50.464 --> 39:51.521
after that day.

39:51.844 --> 39:54.717
I'm not sure what you
mean, and I'm sorry,

39:54.742 --> 39:57.887
but I really need to get inside
to my daughters and off my feet.

39:57.912 --> 39:59.905
- Okay?
- Just one last thing.

40:00.561 --> 40:03.848
If there's no relationship
with Frances Thorp,

40:04.637 --> 40:06.446
what were you guys
doing together yesterday?

40:07.311 --> 40:08.581
At that diner?

40:20.355 --> 40:23.323
Peppermint for the stomach?
Or chamomile for sleep?

40:24.167 --> 40:25.625
Peppermint is fine.

40:28.540 --> 40:29.574
So...

40:30.465 --> 40:32.498
what did this Detective
Hull have to say?

40:32.834 --> 40:35.701
That he saw us at the diner, which means

40:35.726 --> 40:38.293
he knows we've seen
each other since Gail's.

40:38.840 --> 40:41.406
(SIGHS) Not our most shining moment.

40:41.609 --> 40:44.362
No, it wasn't. And I'm sorry.

40:47.219 --> 40:48.485
I appreciate that, Mary.

40:57.224 --> 40:59.491
The truth is, we need to stick together.

41:00.741 --> 41:02.655
If one of us goes down,
so does the other.

41:05.245 --> 41:08.595
What did you say... to this detective?

41:08.620 --> 41:10.917
That we met that day at Gail's,

41:10.942 --> 41:14.076
and then afterwards, and
then decided to work together.

41:15.105 --> 41:18.264
So you're now referring terminal
patients from the hospital

41:18.289 --> 41:20.945
to Joys like Annie did.

41:22.202 --> 41:23.270
That's smart.

41:23.922 --> 41:25.050
Very smart.

41:26.088 --> 41:28.986
Well, you... you
covered for me at Gail's.

41:29.721 --> 41:31.857
So, I'm doing the same
with you, with Dorothy.

41:34.025 --> 41:35.659
But we still need to make sure

41:35.875 --> 41:37.028
that he believes me.

41:37.867 --> 41:39.070
For both our sakes.

41:41.055 --> 41:42.400
How do we do that?

41:45.024 --> 41:46.991
I think you should bring me a patient,

41:47.016 --> 41:48.940
someone we could admit to Joys.

41:50.321 --> 41:52.139
Just in case he's still watching.

41:53.012 --> 41:56.246
(TENSE MUSIC)

42:16.435 --> 42:18.935
(TENSE MUSIC)

42:29.187 --> 42:30.480
She's gonna do it.

42:31.016 --> 42:33.292
She's bringing someone
to Joys this week.

42:34.486 --> 42:35.852
She'll let me know when.

42:37.189 --> 42:38.721
This is gonna work.

42:39.542 --> 42:40.660
Trust me.

42:41.441 --> 42:43.472
Hull obviously thinks
you're working together.

42:43.497 --> 42:45.063
At least now it'll look legit.

42:48.004 --> 42:50.599
I did what you said
today at the hospice,

42:51.293 --> 42:52.535
and it was...

42:53.598 --> 42:54.837
it was awful.

42:55.692 --> 42:58.241
I sat there with a man as he died

42:59.176 --> 43:01.611
slowly and painfully.

43:03.067 --> 43:05.109
It wasn't how it's supposed to be.

43:06.413 --> 43:09.452
What I do is right. It's good.

43:12.272 --> 43:14.091
I'm not gonna let anyone stop me.

43:15.382 --> 43:16.912
Especially not Frances.

43:21.098 --> 43:23.832
- (SIGHS)
- (ENGINE STARTS)

